See manual_full_00_README.txt for the tier legend. Every example in jq's Regular Expressions chapter (17 total, across test/match/capture/scan/split(regex)/splits/sub/gsub) needs pattern matching that Python's `re` module would provide -- and $pyrun's import access is unconfirmed (never tried an `import` or module-qualified call in anything you've confirmed so far). Rather than write 17 near-identical "BLOCKED: needs re" rows, one representative example per function below, all genuinely blocked on the same single open question: does $pyrun= have import access, and if so to what.

[RX-001-test]
LEVEL=logic
JQ = test("foo")
INPUT = "foo"
GOLD = true
JFTL = TODO
COMMENT=BLOCKED: needs `re.search`/`re.match` (or Python's `in`/`==` for this literal-substring-only case, which actually WOULD work here without import -- "$pyrun= 'foo' in _" -- but that's cheating the regex engine, not testing test() as a regex facility, so not claiming it as a real port).

